{
  "_readme": [
    "Keyword vocabulary for context.mjs. Three tag groups:",
    "  dishTypes — matched against recipe TITLES (what kind of dish is this?)",
    "  methods   — matched against recipe DIRECTIONS (how is it cooked?)",
    "  cuisines  — matched against recipe TITLES (dish-name markers included)",
    "Matching is word-boundary, case-insensitive, with optional plural 's'/'es'.",
    "Entries prefixed with '!' are EXCLUSIONS: the tag fires only when a positive",
    "keyword matches AND no exclusion phrase appears anywhere in the title. This is",
    "how bare 'pie' can tag desserts without 'Chicken Pot Pie' riding along.",
    "Exclusions were tuned against the full-corpus audit (audit-tag-precision.mjs,",
    "output/tag-precision-report.md) — re-run it after editing keywords.",
    "Note the plural regex '(e?s)?' does NOT cover y-plurals: 'patty' misses",
    "'patties' — add the 'pattie' spelling explicitly when it matters.",
    "Tag names are display-ready — they appear verbatim in the app UI.",
    "Keep keywords high-precision: a tag should only fire when it's clearly right.",
    "Ambiguous words (e.g. bare 'curry' spans Indian/Thai/Japanese) are omitted on purpose."
  ],
